      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Embracing the stillness is just a way of saying that you're okay with being here, with the pain, and with the loneliness. It's okay to feel helpless because it's a normal part of this journey. You don't have to have control over everything. Sometimes, letting go of that control can actually give you some peace. Maybe it's time to find a new way to live, even if it's just in your mind. You don't have to wait for your body to decide anything. You can take control of your thoughts and your feelings. It's okay to let go of the need for control. It's okay to just be here.",
      "source": "target",
